{"id":"10948","name":"List Shortcut Folders","tagline":"A really simple way to get a list of your folders in the Shortcuts app","icon":"ios14 c3679049983 g59737","latest":"31796","description":"\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>When playing with the new (macOS 12) <code>shortcuts</code> Terminal command, which allows getting the list of shortcut folders with the command</p>\n<pre><code>shortcuts list --folders\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>I got an idea for doing something equivalent for iOS. It worked on my first try, and it works in iOS 14 too.</p>\n<p>When run without input, the shortcut is a demo and for presentation purposes the output is a multiline text. Run it with any input to silently get the folder list.</p>\n\t\t\t\t","releasenotes":"<p><strong>1.1.0 - Feb. 12, 2022, 12:03 p.m.</strong></p><p>Modified to work as a function (any input returns the list silently)</p>"}